      </p>
      <ul>
        <li>Total extra paid with 15-year over 15 years: $615 × 180 months = $110,700</li>
        <li>Interest savings: $219,780</li>
        <li>Net benefit: <strong>$109,080 in pocket</strong> (plus owning your home 15 years sooner)</li>
      </ul>
      <p>
        That $109,000 is real money you keep — but only if you can actually afford the higher payment consistently for 15 years without compromising other financial priorities.
      </p>

